      • replaceCaseInsensitive

        public String replaceCaseInsensitive(String doc0,
                                     String old,
                                     String newterm)
        Replaces old term in doc0 with newterm. This method is case insensitive, as the name suggests.
        Parameters:
        doc0 - The text where the term has to be replaced.
        old - The piece of text to replaced.
        newterm - The term which will replace old
        Returns:
        The string with the occurences of old replaced by newterm
